spec: mp3331
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.managers.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 669 (mp3331): __iand__, __ior__, __ixor__ dict-presence (in-place &=, |=, ^=) for multiprocessing types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: multiprocessing.Process, pool.Pool, pool.AsyncResult, pool.MapResult, managers.SyncManager, managers.BaseListProxy, managers._BaseDictProxy, managers._BaseSetProxy."
    - "Key finding (__iand__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __iand__. In-place bitwise AND (__iand__, &=) is the augmented assignment variant of __and__. Wave 661 confirmed __and__ is false for all 8 mp types. managers._BaseSetProxy is the most nuanced case: it proxies set, and set defines __and__ for set intersection (s & t). However, _BaseSetProxy.__dict__ does NOT contain __and__ (confirmed false in wave 661) — the proxy forwards set-algebra read operations through __getattr__ routing but does not define in-place operators in its own __dict__. Therefore __iand__ is equally absent from _BaseSetProxy.__dict__. multiprocessing.Process: subprocess lifecycle manager; process &= n is not a defined Python expression. pool.Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: work-dispatch and result-handle types; no bitwise data model. managers._BaseDictProxy: proxies dict — dict defines no __iand__. managers.BaseListProxy: proxies list — list defines no __iand__. managers.SyncManager: server process; no in-place bitwise AND defined."
    - "Key finding (__ior__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __ior__. In-place bitwise OR (__ior__, |=) is the augmented assignment variant of __or__. Wave 661 confirmed __or__ is false for all 8 mp types. managers._BaseSetProxy key note: set defines __ior__ for in-place set union (s |= t), and Python 3.9 introduced __ior__ on dict for in-place merging. However, _BaseSetProxy.__dict__ does NOT contain __ior__ — the proxy does not forward in-place operations to the managed set object. In-place operators like |= would need to rebind the local variable to the result, which is semantically incompatible with a proxy object that wraps a remote managed object. Therefore __ior__ is absent from _BaseSetProxy.__dict__ despite set itself defining it. managers._BaseDictProxy: dict defines __ior__ (Python 3.9+) for in-place merging, but _BaseDictProxy.__dict__ does not contain __ior__ — the dict proxy does not forward this in-place operation. multiprocessing.Process/pool.Pool/pool.AsyncResult/pool.MapResult/managers.SyncManager: no in-place bitwise OR defined."
    - "Key finding (__ixor__): all 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __ixor__. In-place bitwise XOR (__ixor__, ^=) is the augmented assignment variant of __xor__. Wave 661 confirmed __xor__ is false for all 8 mp types. managers._BaseSetProxy key note: set defines __ixor__ for in-place symmetric difference (s ^= t). However, _BaseSetProxy.__dict__ does NOT contain __ixor__ — the proxy does not forward in-place set algebra operations. This is consistent with __iand__ and __ior__: _BaseSetProxy proxies set, which has __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ for in-place set algebra, but the proxy dict does not contain them. No in-place proxy forwarding is implemented. managers._BaseDictProxy: dict defines no __ixor__. managers.BaseListProxy: list defines no __ixor__. multiprocessing.Process/pool.Pool/pool.AsyncResult/pool.MapResult/managers.SyncManager: no in-place XOR defined."
    - "All 24 values in this wave are false. The _BaseSetProxy finding is the most analytically significant: set itself defines all three in-place set-algebra operators (__iand__, __ior__, __ixor__), yet _BaseSetProxy.__dict__ contains none of them. The proxy does not forward in-place operations. In-place operators would require rebinding the caller's variable, which is semantically incompatible with a transparent proxy over a managed remote object."
    - "Cross-wave summary for mp subjects:"
    - "  Wave 658 (mp3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — BaseListProxy __add__=true, __mul__=true; others false."
    - "  Wave 659 (mp3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 660 (mp3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 661 (mp3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 662 (mp3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 663 (mp3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 664 (mp3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 665 (mp3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 666 (mp3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 667 (mp3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 668 (mp3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 8."
    - "  Wave 669 (mp3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 8."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __iand__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__iand__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __iand__.
# In-place bitwise AND (__iand__, &=) is the augmented assignment variant
#   of __and__. Wave 661 confirmed __and__ is false for all 8 mp types.
# managers._BaseSetProxy: proxies set, and set defines __and__ for set
#   intersection (s & t) and __iand__ for in-place intersection (s &= t).
#   However, _BaseSetProxy.__dict__ does NOT contain __iand__ — the proxy
#   does not forward in-place set algebra operations. All false.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: dict defines no __iand__. False.
# managers.BaseListProxy: list defines no __iand__. False.
# Process/Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult: process-management and result-handle
#   types; in-place bitwise AND is not defined for any of them.
# managers.SyncManager: server process; no in-place bitwise AND defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table mp3331.iand:
  description: "multiprocessing types __iand__ dict-presence checks; wave 669"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: mp3331

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - ["mp3331001", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.Process.__dict__,                 "__iand__"], false]
    - ["mp3331002", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.Pool.__dict__,               "__iand__"], false]
    - ["mp3331003", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.AsyncResult.__dict__,        "__iand__"], false]
    - ["mp3331004", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.pool.MapResult.__dict__,          "__iand__"], false]
    - ["mp3331005", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.SyncManager.__dict__,    "__iand__"], false]
    - ["mp3331006", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers.BaseListProxy.__dict__,  "__iand__"], false]
    - ["mp3331007", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseDictProxy.__dict__, "__iand__"], false]
    - ["mp3331008", operator.contains, [multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy.__dict__,  "__iand__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __ior__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__ior__')
#
# All 8 multiprocessing classes return false for __ior__.
# In-place bitwise OR (__ior__, |=) is the augmented assignment variant
#   of __or__. Wave 661 confirmed __or__ is false for all 8 mp types.
# managers._BaseSetProxy key note: set defines __ior__ for in-place set
#   union (s |= t). However, _BaseSetProxy.__dict__ does NOT contain __ior__
#   — the proxy does not forward in-place operations to the managed set.
#   In-place operators require rebinding the caller's local variable, which
#   is semantically incompatible with a transparent proxy over a managed
#   remote object. Therefore __ior__ is absent from _BaseSetProxy.__dict__
#   despite set itself defining it.
# managers._BaseDictProxy: dict defines __ior__ (Python 3.9+) for in-place
#   merging (d |= other), but _BaseDictProxy.__dict__ does not contain __ior__
#   — the dict proxy does not forward this in-place operation. False.
# managers.BaseListProxy: list defines no __ior__. False.
# Process/Pool/AsyncResult/MapResult/SyncManager: no in-place bitwise OR
#   defined for any of these types.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table mp3331.ior:
  description: "multiprocessing types __ior__ dict-presence checks; wave 669"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
